        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-13 19:58:38.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1\n\nJohnson,\nI see a few more issues. \n\nThe base_*_rackspace.env files contain parameters like:\nvpp_source_repo_url: https://gerrit.fd.io/r/vpp\nvpp_source_repo_branch: stable/1704\nvpp_patch_url: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/11083/5/vnfs/vCPE/vpp-radius-client-for-vbng/src/patches/Vpp-Integrate-FreeRADIUS-Client-for-vBNG.patch\n\nIn the corresponding bash script, those parameters are used like:\ngit clone ${VPP_SOURCE_REPO_URL} -b ${VPP_SOURCE_REPO_BRANCH} vpp\nwget -O Vpp-Integrate-FreeRADIUS-Client-for-vBNG.patch ${VPP_PATCH_URL}\n\nThe issues are:\n1) the repo URL and branch don't exist. Are you planning to ask TSC/LF for the creation of new repos in Gerrit for VPP-based software?\n2) the patch URL refers to an outstanding code commit, not a file. As such, the wget command will likely return the Gerrit HTML page linked to that commit.\n\nCould you please correct those parameters in all the env files? Or, if that is correct, could you please explain?\n\nThanks,\nMarco",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
      {
        "id": "79b20354acbacd74fa682dc4060406a1dad0f29a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 231,
          "name": "Johnson Li",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "johnson.li@intel.com",
          "username": "xunleer"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-09-14 01:26:17.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5:\n\nThe issues are:\n1) the repo URL and branch don't exist. Are you planning to ask TSC/LF for the creation of new repos in Gerrit for VPP-based software?\n[JL]: >> The branch already exists, i can use the command \ngit clone  https://gerrit.fd.io/r/vpp -b stable/1704 vpp\nto get the codes. So you may have a try. \n\n2) the patch URL refers to an outstanding code commit, not a file. As such, the wget command will likely return the Gerrit HTML page linked to that commit.\nCould you please correct those parameters in all the env files? Or, if that is correct, could you please explain?\n[JL]: >> I don't know where to publish the patch files, so i use this link for the patches.",
        "patchset_number": 5
      },
